cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.COMM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with evaluating the performance of different detection methods in a multi-cell massive MIMO system with imperfect CSI. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper considers the uplink of a multi-cell system with multiple users communicating with a base station. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper deals with the effects of pilot contamination on the system performance. 
- cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is another possibility as the paper considers a communication system with multiple cells and users. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still a possibility as the paper deals with a massive MIMO system with multiple antennas at the base station.
